      "message": "The passed-in \"device\" bounds parameter/behavior is a little tricky. Could we simplify this API?\n\ne.g.\n\nenum BoundsState {\n    kEmpty,\n    kNormal,\n    kInsideOut,\n};\n\nBoundsState bounds(SkRect* bounds);\n\nIf the clients want to later intersect the returned bounds with some other rect, they can always do that separately.\n\n---\n\nOr, and this question is for Brian as well, do we think the ALL clients wanting to query a clipstack of its bounds will want to intersect with something, and therefore requiring a dev-bounds makes sense?\n\nOr, should we instead seed the clipstack with its host\u0027s device_bounds up front, and so all rectangles can automatically take this into account?",
